quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  23,82,"They said, "
  23,83,"We have been promised this, we and our forefathers, before; this is not but legends of the former peoples."
  23,84,"Say, [O Muḥammad], "
  24,64,"Unquestionably, to Allāh belongs whatever is in the heavens and earth. Already He knows that upon which you [stand]{1} and [knows] the Day{2} when they will be returned to Him and He will inform them of what they have done. And Allāh is Knowing of all things.",footnotes:1:i.e., your position - the basis for your actions (whether sincere faith or hypocrisy) and the condition of your souls.,footnotes:2:The meaning can also be rendered \"...and [let them beware of] the Day...\"
  25,28,"Oh, woe to me! I wish I had not taken that one{1} as a friend.",footnotes:1:The person who misguided him.
  25,29,"He led me away from the remembrance{1} after it had come to me. And ever is Satan, to man, a deserter.",footnotes:1:i.e., the Qur’ān or the remembrance of Allāh.Forsaking him once he has led him into evil.
  25,30,"And the Messenger has said, ",footnotes:1:i.e., avoiding it, not listening to or understanding it, not living by it, or preferring something else to it.
  26,1,"Ṭā, Seen, Meem.{1}",footnotes:1:See footnote to 2:1.
  26,2,"These are the verses of the clear Book."
  26,3,"Perhaps, [O Muḥammad], you would kill yourself with grief that they will not be believers."